<h2>The Enterprise Stack Architecture</h2>
<p>Most enterprise sales teams don't use a single tool — they build a stack. The most common enterprise configuration in 2026 looks like this:</p>

<table class="guide-comparison-table">
<thead>
<tr><th>Layer</th><th>Tool</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td><strong>CRM</strong></td><td>Salesforce or HubSpot</td><td>System of record for all deal and contact data</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Data</strong></td><td>ZoomInfo or Apollo</td><td>Prospecting database and contact enrichment</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Enrichment</strong></td><td>Clay</td><td>Waterfall enrichment, intent signals, AI research</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Engagement</strong></td><td>Outreach or Salesloft</td><td>Sequencing, cadence management, rep activity</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Intelligence</strong></td><td>Gong</td><td>Call recording, deal risk, coaching, forecasting</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>The total cost of this stack for a 50-rep team typically runs $400K–$700K/year in software alone, which is why the "consolidation vs. best-of-breed" debate is so active in enterprise sales leadership. Teams that can replace Salesforce + Outreach with HubSpot Enterprise often cut stack costs by 30–40% with acceptable trade-offs in depth.</p>

<h2>How to Run the Evaluation</h2>
<p>Enterprise tool evaluations typically take 8–16 weeks from initial shortlist to contract. The most common failure mode is evaluating tools in isolation rather than as a system. Here's the framework that produces better outcomes:</p>
<ol>
  <li><strong>Define your integration requirements first.</strong> What's your CRM? What data flows need to be bidirectional? What identity provider handles SSO? These answers eliminate tools before you waste time on demos.</li>
  <li><strong>Run a parallel pilot, not sequential.</strong> Test 2–3 tools simultaneously with the same rep cohort on the same ICP. Sequential testing introduces too many variables.</li>
  <li><strong>Measure what matters to your business.</strong> For engagement platforms: sequence reply rates, meetings booked per rep, and time-to-first-touch. For intelligence: forecast accuracy, deal risk identification rate, and coaching adoption.</li>
  <li><strong>Involve IT and Legal early.</strong> Security reviews and DPA negotiations add 4–8 weeks. Starting them after you've chosen a tool is the most common cause of delayed rollouts.</li>
</ol>

